					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">tokumaru wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">It just occurred me that maybe a lua script can simulate this automatic switching in emulators... I might give this a try.</div><br />Something like this should work for Mesen:<div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">local mirroringReg = 0xA000<br />local horizontalMirroring = 1<br />local verticalMirroring = 0<br />local lastAddr = 0<br /><br />function switchNametables(addr)&nbsp; <br />&nbsp; if (addr &amp; 0x3FF) &lt; 0x3C0 then --ignore attribute fetches<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; if (lastAddr &amp; 0x20) ~= (addr &amp; 0x20) then<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; if addr &amp; 0x20 == 0 then<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; emu.write(mirroringReg, horizontalMirroring, emu.memType.cpu)<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; else <br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; emu.write(mirroringReg, verticalMirroring, emu.memType.cpu)<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; end&nbsp; <br />&nbsp; &nbsp; end<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; lastAddr = addr<br />&nbsp; end<br />end<br /><br />emu.addMemoryCallback(switchNametables, emu.memCallbackType.ppuRead, 0x2000, 0x2FFF)</div><br /><br />Obviously this is just a test (for MMC3) but you should be able to tweak it easily enough for any other mapper.<br /><br />Result: <div class="attachtitle">Attachment:</div><div class="attachcontent">
			<a href="./download/file.php?id=12876&amp;mode=view"><img src="./download/file.php?id=12876&amp;t=1" alt="smb3.png" /></a><br />
			<span class="gensmall">smb3.png [ 20.81 KiB | Viewed 1493 times ]</span>
		

		<br />
	</div></div>

